---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import AffiliateLink from '../components/AffiliateLink.astro';

const meta = {
  title: 'Durable.co Review: AI Landing Pages in 10 Minutes (Tested)',
  description: 'I tested Durable.co for 3 weeks. Can AI really generate a complete landing page with good copy? Here\'s my honest review with real examples.',
  image: '/og-image.svg',
  keywords: ['Durable.co review', 'Durable.co AI', 'AI landing page builder', 'AI website generator', 'Durable.co pricing'],
};
---

<Layout {...meta}>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-[#FEF9F3] py-12 sm:py-16 md:py-20">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
      <p class="text-[10px] sm:text-xs font-black text-[#E07A5F] mb-4 tracking-[0.3em] uppercase">
        3 Weeks Tested · Real Projects · Honest Review
      </p>

      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-black mb-6 leading-tight">
        Durable.co Review
      </h1>

      <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl md:text-3xl text-gray-700 mb-8 font-bold">
        AI Landing Pages in 10 Minutes
      </h2>

      <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl md:text-2xl text-gray-700 mb-8">
        I tested Durable.co for 3 weeks. Built real landing pages. Compared with alternatives. Here's my honest review: what's great, what's not, and who should use it.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-[#E07A5F]/10 border-2 border-[#E07A5F] rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
          Quick verdict: Durable generates the best AI copy of any landing page builder. But design flexibility is limited. Great for non-developers who need copy-first pages.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          Read on for the full breakdown, real examples, and whether Durable is right for you.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What is Durable -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      What Durable.co Actually Does
    </h2>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
      <AffiliateLink href="https://durable.co/" className="text-purple-600 hover:text-purple-800 underline">Durable.co</AffiliateLink> is an AI-powered landing page builder. You describe your business, it generates a complete landing page with copy, design, and images.
    </p>

    <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6 my-8">
      <p class="font-bold mb-3">Core features:</p>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
        <li><strong>AI copy generation</strong> — Headlines, sections, CTAs based on your business</li>
        <li><strong>Design templates</strong> — Modern layouts, customization options</li>
        <li><strong>Hosting included</strong> — One-click publish, custom domain support</li>
        <li><strong>Analytics</strong> — Built-in tracking (Pro plan and above)</li>
        <li><strong>Fast generation</strong> — Complete page in 5-15 minutes</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
      <strong>The promise:</strong> Describe your business, get a complete landing page. No coding required. No design skills needed. Just answer questions and publish.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- My Test -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      My Test: Real Landing Page, Real Business
    </h2>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
      I created a landing page for a fictional SaaS product called "TaskFlow" (project management tool for freelancers). Same prompt across all AI builders for fair comparison.
    </p>

    <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6 my-8">
      <p class="font-bold mb-3">The prompt I gave Durable:</p>
      <div class="bg-white border-2 border-gray-300 rounded-lg p-4 font-mono text-sm">
        <p class="text-gray-800">"Build a landing page for TaskFlow, a project management tool for freelancers. Target audience: independent freelancers, consultants, contractors. Key features: time tracking, client management, invoice generation, project templates. Main benefit: organize freelance work in one place, stop dropping balls."</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
      <strong>Time to generate:</strong> About 8 minutes from prompt to complete page.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- What Durable Did Well -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      What Durable Did Well
    </h2>

    <div class="bg-green-50 rounded-xl p-6 my-8">
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
        <li><strong>Excellent copy</strong> — Specific headlines, clear value props, compelling CTAs</li>
        <li><strong>Brand voice</strong> — Felt like a real product, not AI-generated template</li>
        <li><strong>Persuasive structure</strong> — Problem → Solution → Features → Pricing → CTA flow</li>
        <li><strong>Fast generation</strong> — 8 minutes to complete page</li>
        <li><strong>Hosting included</strong> — One-click publish, custom domain easy</li>
        <li><strong>Good mobile responsive</strong> — Looks great on phone automatically</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
      <strong>Copy quality example:</strong> Durable's headline: "Stop Juggling Freelance Chaos. One Tool for Everything." vs v0.dev's generic: "Transform Your Freelance Business Management." Durable wins on copy every time.
    </p>

    <div class="bg-green-50 border-l-4 border-green-600 rounded-r-xl p-6 my-8">
      <p class="font-bold mb-3">The standout feature:</p>
      <p class="text-gray-700">Durable's AI copy is genuinely good. Not just grammatically correct—persuasive. It speaks to customer pain points. It makes specific promises. It feels like it was written by a copywriter, not an AI.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What Durable Struggled With -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      What Durable Struggled With
    </h2>

    <div class="bg-red-50 rounded-xl p-6 my-8">
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
        <li><strong>Limited design flexibility</strong> — Can't easily customize beyond templates</li>
        <li><strong>Formulaic layouts</strong> — Most pages look similar (Durable "style")</li>
        <li><strong>No code export</strong> — Stuck in Durable ecosystem</li>
        <li><strong>Limited sections</strong> — Can't add custom sections easily</li>
        <li><strong>Generic images</strong> — Stock photos feel repetitive</li>
        <li><strong>SEO limited</strong> — Basic meta tags, no advanced optimization</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
      <strong>The main limitation:</strong> If you want unique design or custom layouts, Durable feels constrained. You're working within their design system, and their design system is recognizable.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Pricing -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Durable.co Pricing
    </h2>

    <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6 my-8">
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
        <li><strong>Free:</strong> 3 sites, Durable branding on footer, basic features</li>
        <li><strong>Pro ($12/month):</strong> Custom domain, remove branding, analytics</li>
        <li><strong>Business ($20/month):</strong> Multiple sites, advanced analytics, priority support</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
      <strong>Value assessment:</strong> Pro plan at $12/month is solid. Hosting included, good copy generation, custom domain. Cheaper than paying separately for hosting + copywriting.
    </p>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
      <strong>Free tier is generous</strong> for testing. 3 sites with Durable branding. Good way to try before you buy.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Who Should Use Durable -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Who Should Use Durable.co
    </h2>

    <div class="bg-[#81B29A]/10 border-2 border-[#81B29A] rounded-xl p-6 my-8">
      <p class="font-bold mb-3">Choose Durable if:</p>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
        <li>• You're <strong>not technical</strong> and can't/don't want to code</li>
        <li>• You care about <strong>copy quality</strong> first, design second</li>
        <li>• You want to be <strong>online quickly</strong> (same day)</li>
        <li>• You don't want to manage hosting separately</li>
        <li>• You're okay with <strong>template-based design</strong></li>
        <li>• You're a <strong>small business owner</strong> or solopreneur</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-red-50 border-2 border-red-500 rounded-xl p-6 my-8">
      <p class="font-bold mb-3">Don't choose Durable if:</p>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
        <li>• You want <strong>full design control</strong> or custom layouts</li>
        <li>• You're a <strong>developer</strong> who wants to edit code</li>
        <li>• You need <strong>complex functionality</strong> beyond landing pages</li>
        <li>• You want to <strong>export code</strong> and host yourself</li>
        <li>• You need <strong>unique design</strong> that doesn't look like a template</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Alternatives -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Durable.co Alternatives
    </h2>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-bold mb-3">v0.dev</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Better design flexibility, code export. Worse copy. Free tier: 100 generations/month. Best for: Developers, code-savvy users.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-bold mb-3">Framer</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Full website builder, great design. AI features are limited. $15/month. Best for: Complete websites, designers.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
      <strong>See full comparisons:</strong>
      <AffiliateLink href="https://v0.dev/" className="text-purple-600 hover:text-purple-800 underline">v0.dev vs Durable</AffiliateLink> |
      <AffiliateLink href="https://www.framer.com/" className="text-purple-600 hover:text-purple-800 underline">Framer vs Durable</AffiliateLink> |
      <AffiliateLink href="https://v0.dev/" className="text-purple-600 hover:text-purple-800 underline">v0.dev vs Framer</AffiliateLink>
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- My Verdict -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      My Verdict After 3 Weeks
    </h2>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
      I use Durable for specific use cases. It's not my primary tool (that's v0.dev), but it fills a gap: quick landing pages with great copy for non-technical projects.
    </p>

    <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6 my-8">
      <p class="font-bold mb-3">I use Durable for:</p>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
        <li>• Quick test landing pages (validate ideas before building)</li>
        <li>• Clients who need copy-first pages (design secondary)</li>
        <li>• Projects where I don't want to touch code</li>
        <li>• MVP landing pages that can be refined later</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
      <strong>Overall rating:</strong> 7.5/10. Excellent copy, easy to use, hosting included. Limited design flexibility keeps it from being a 10/10.
    </p>

    <div class="text-center my-8">
      <AffiliateLink
        href="https://durable.co/"
        className="inline-block bg-purple-600 hover:bg-purple-700 text-white font-black py-3 px-6 rounded-lg mr-2"
      >
        Try Durable.co Free
      </AffiliateLink>
    </div>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
      <strong>Final thought:</strong> If you're non-technical and need a landing page NOW with good copy, Durable is the best choice. If you want design flexibility or code control, look elsewhere.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Related -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-black mb-6 text-gray-900">
      More AI Website Builder Reviews
    </h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <a href="/vs/v0-vs-durable" class="block bg-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">v0.dev vs Durable</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Design vs copy quality comparison.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/vs/framer-vs-durable" class="block bg-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Framer vs Durable</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Full website builder comparison.</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
